diff:1189516175:1189516175:=1,233d0%0a%3c There are few things that test you manhood like facing down an enemy on the field of battle. It takes rigorous training and discipline to become an honored warrior on the field. Work hard enough and you will find people know your name, and it has become synonymous with dignity, honor, and fair play.%0a%3c %0a%3c Yeah, if you're looking for that shinizle, you're totally in the wrong place. I'm going to teach you to sneak up on your opponent in the dark, suckerpunch him, and gut him from crotch to sternum so you can play with his glistening entrails. Fingerpainting with your enemy's viscera while laughing hysterically is much more intimidating. Just ask the British how well fair play worked for them in the American Revolutionary War.%0a%3c %0a%3c Before you start pillaging and burning you must learn somethings about your weapons and its usage.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c Not all ships are made equal!%0a%3c %0a%3c One of the problems with balanced fleet doctrine is that it tends to make people think they need to use ships that they have no need for in a fleet, giving their enemies an opportunity to destroy them more efficiently. Balance is good, yes, but that does mean you should be building frigates and including them in your fleets to disperse the damage. Let's take a look at all of your units and their applications. While some units are better than others, most have something they do well.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c Fighters: These are the staple of all fleets in AE-- defense, offense, everything. Fighters are the single most efficient ship in the game. The damage they absorb per credit is unparalleled. That makes fighters your #1 unit for use as cannon fodder. When we say you can never have too many fighters, we're being quite literal. A fleet that runs out of fighters will take far higher losses, and can be defeated in detail for obscene exchange rates by anyone who manages to catch them. Build thousands for base defense, and then keep b